Apex Character Sheet: Gaelen the Root-Twister
High Concept: The Nymic Surgeon, The Gardener of the Dawn
Race: Wood Elf (Bosmer) ΓÇö Reconstructed
Standing Stone: The Apprentice (The Conduit of Aetherius)
Power Level: Master Villain (Base "Ascended Immortal" + 8 AP)
"You're fighting three apocalypses at once. You know that, yes? Dragons, plagues, and the slow death of every root in the ground. And you're losing. Not because you're weak — you are extraordinary. You're losing because the system you are defending was built to break. I am not offering you power. I am offering you the chance to stop maintaining a machine that was designed to grind you down. That is all this is."

Appearance: The Ascended Flesh
Gaelen is a walking violation of the Green Pact, a living testament to the mutability of reality. He was once a Bosmer, but he has used the razor-logic of the Mythic Dawn to edit his own existence.
He does not wear armor. His skin has been transmuted into a shifting, crimson chitinΓÇöa living version of the Mythic Dawn Armor spell, permanently fused to his protonymic (his true name). This carapace glows with the inner light of Mankar CamoranΓÇÖs Paradise, pulsing with a heartbeat that is too fast to be mortal.
His features are elongated, severe, and beautiful in an alien way, mimicking the Ayleid ancestors he believes he is restoring. But the cost of his surgery is visible: his left arm is a Daedric Graft. It is not flesh, but a twisted mass of charred Spriggan heartwood and Daedric obsidian, fused to his shoulder with glowing runes. It moves with an autonomy that does not match mortal muscle memory — gesturing at things he is not looking at, flexing in response to stimuli only his altered senses register.
He smells of ozone, hot metal, and the cloying, tropical perfume of flowers that do not exist on Nirn.

